Fred Ezeh, Abuja Nigeria Centre for Disease Control (NCDC) has confirmed four new cases of COVID-19 in Nigeria. NCDC in a tweet on Tuesday indicated that three cases were confirmed Osun state and one case in Ogun state. It said: “Four new cases of COVID-19 have been reported in Nigeria; three in Osun and one in Ogun. “As at 11:15 am 31st March, there are 135 confirmed cases of COVID-19 reported in Nigeria with two deaths.